{{term|term= '''[[Biot number]]'''}}{{defn|defn=The '''Biot number''' ('''Bi''') is a [[dimensionless quantity]] used in heat transfer calculations. It is named after the eighteenth century French physicist [[Jean-Baptiste Biot]] (1774–1862), and gives a simple index of the ratio of the heat transfer resistances ''inside of'' and ''at the surface of'' a body. This ratio determines whether or not the temperatures inside a body will vary significantly in space, while the body heats or cools over time, from a thermal gradient applied to its surface.}}
